There is a lot of price fixing going on in this town, there is never one gas station cheaper than the other and they all drop their prices within an hour of each other when they do drop. A couple of years ago there was even an "investigation" by police about price fixing, but of course nothing would come from that.

I filled up the other day in St. Catharines for  79.3 /L.  I feel the pain of motorists who are paying $1.00 / L.  When gas was 1.30 /L it cost $180.00 to fill my truck.  143 L tank - OUCH!  I'll never complain about gas prices, since I've been working in the oil sands.  In 2015 my income was reduced to 50% of 2014 due to massive layoffs in the oil industry.  As HTHM stated low oil prices have crippled the economy of Canada!  My company employed as many as 40 crane operators in 2013 & 2014.  Today there are only 4 operators at work!!
